 <section xml:id="sec-shapley-shubik-power-index">
  <title>Shapley-Shubik Power Index</title>
  
  <p>
      The Shapley-Shubik Power Index is another method for measuring voting power in weighted voting systems.
  </p>
  
  <definition xml:id="def-shapley-shubik">
    <title>Shapley-Shubik Power Index</title>
    <statement>
      <p>
        The <term>Shapley-Shubik Power Index</term> measures the power of each player based on the number of times they are pivotal when players join a coalition in all possible orders.
      </p>
    </statement>
  </definition>
 </section>

